SUMMARY: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
This document proposes the adoption of a new airworthiness directive (AD) that is applicable to certain Boeing Model
747 series airplanes. This proposal would require inspections to detect cracking in certain fuselage upper deck
tension ties, and repair or modification of any cracked tension ties. This proposal is prompted by reports of fatigue
cracking in tension ties. The actions specified by the proposed AD are intended to prevent failure of two or more tension
ties and the resultant rapid decompression of the airplane.
