<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart A_General Provisions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.1 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Purpose. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) This part establishes procedures and criteria for the Secretary's recognition of accrediting agencies.
The purpose of the Secretary's recognition of agencies is to assure that these agencies are, for the purposes of the
Higher Education Act of 1965, as amended (HEA), or for other Federal purposes, reliable authorities as to the quality
of education or training offered by the institutions of higher education or the higher education programs they accredit.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary's recognition of an accrediting agency is based on the Secretary's determination that the agency
satisfies the requirements of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary grants recognition only to those agencies that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Accredit institutions of higher education for the purpose of enabling them to establish eligibility to participate
in HEA programs; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Accredit institutions of higher education or higher education programs for the purpose of enabling them to establish
eligibility to participate in other programs administered by the Department or by other Federal agencies.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.2 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Definitions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The following definitions apply to terms used in this part: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Accreditation
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the status of public recognition that an accrediting agency grants to an educational institution or program
that meets the agency's established qualifications and standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Accrediting agency
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 or 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
agency
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a legal entity, or that part of a legal entity, that conducts accrediting activities through voluntary, non-Federal
peer evaluations and makes decisions concerning the accreditation or preaccreditation status of institutions,
programs, or both. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Act
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means the Higher Education Act of 1965, as amended. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Adverse accrediting action 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the denial, withdrawal, suspension, or termination of accreditation or preaccreditation, or any comparable
accrediting action an agency may take against an institution or program, except that placing an institution or program
on probation or issuing a show cause order against an institution or program is not an adverse accrediting action unless
it is so defined by the accrediting agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Advisory Committee 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the National Advisory Committee on Institutional Quality and Integrity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Branch campus
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 means a location of an institution of higher education that is geographically apart from and independent of the main
campus of the institution. The Secretary considers a location of an institution to be independent of the main campus
if the location (1) is permanent in nature; (2) offers courses in educational programs leading to a degree, certificate,
or other recognized educational credential; (3) has its own faculty and administrative or supervisory organization;
and (4) has its own budgetary and hiring authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Designated Department official 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the official in the Department of Education to whom the Secretary has delegated the responsibilities indicated
in this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Institution of higher education 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
or 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
institution 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means an educational institution that qualifies or may qualify as an eligible institution under 34 CFR part 600. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Institutional accrediting agency 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means an agency that accredits institutions of higher education. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Nationally recognized accrediting agency, nationally recognized agency,
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 or 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
recognized agency 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means an accrediting agency that is recognized by the Secretary under this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Part 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means part 602 of title 34 of the Code of Federal Regulations governing the Secretary's procedures and criteria for
the recognition of accrediting agencies. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Preaccreditation 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the status of public recognition that an accrediting agency grants to an institution or program for a limited
period of time that signifies that the agency has determined that the institution or program is progressing towards
accreditation and is likely to attain accreditation within a reasonable period of time. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Prebaccalaureate vocational education 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means vocational education that leads to a certificate, degree, or other credential that is less than a bachelor's
degree. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Program 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means a postsecondary educational program offered by an institution that leads to an academic or professional degree,
vocational certificate, or other recognized educational credential. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00062 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Programmatic accrediting agency 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means an agency that accredits specific educational programs that prepare students for entry into a profession,
occupation, or vocation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Representative of the public 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means a person who is not (1) an employee, member of the governing board, owner, or shareholder of, or consultant to,
an institution or program that either is accredited by the agency or has applied for accreditation; or (2) a member
of any trade association or membership organization related to, affiliated with, or associated with the accrediting
agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Secretary 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means the Secretary of the U.S. Department of Education or any official or employee of the Department acting for the
Secretary under a delegation of authority. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
State 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means a State of the Union, American Samoa, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the District of Columbia, Guam, the Trust
Territory of the Pacific Islands, the Virgin Islands, and the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Teach-out agreement 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means a written agreement between accredited institutions that provides for the equitable treatment of students
if one of those institutions stops offering an educational program before all students enrolled in that program complete
the program. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Title IV, HEA program 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means any of the programs set forth in 34 CFR 668.1(c). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Vocational education 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
means education or training that prepares students for gainful employment in a recognized occupation.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.3 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Organization and membership. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Secretary recognizes only the accrediting agencies described in paragraph (b) of this section that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Accredit institutions of higher education or higher education programs for the purpose described in &sect;601.1(b);
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Satisfy the criteria for Secretarial recognition contained in subpart C of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The accrediting agencies referred to in paragraph (a) of this section are_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A State agency that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Has as a principal purpose the accrediting of institutions of higher education, higher education programs, or
both; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has been listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency on or before October 1, 1991; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) An accrediting agency that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Has a voluntary membership of institutions of higher education; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has as a principal purpose the accrediting of institutions of higher education to enable them to participate
in programs authorized under this Act; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Satisfies the ``separate and independent'' requirements contained in paragraph (c) of this section; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) An accrediting agency that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Has a voluntary membership; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has as its principal purpose the accrediting of higher education programs, or higher education programs and
institutions of higher education to enable them to participate in Federal programs not authorized under this Act;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) An accrediting agency that, for purposes of determining eligibility for Title IV, HEA programs_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i)(A) Has a voluntary membership of individuals participating in a profession; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Has as its principal purpose the accrediting of programs within institutions that are accredited by another nationally
recognized accrediting agency; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii)(A) Satisfies the ``separate and independent'' requirements contained in paragraph (c) of this section; or

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Obtains a waiver from the Secretary under paragraph (e) of this section of the ``separate and independent'' requirements
contained in paragraph (c) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) For purposes of this section, ``separate and independent'' means that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The members of the agency's decision-making body_who make its accrediting decisions, establish its accreditation
policies, or both_are not elected or selected by the board or chief executive officer of any related, associated,
or affiliated trade association or membership organization; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) At least one member of the agency's decision-making body is a representative of the public, with no less than one-seventh
of the body consisting of representatives of the public; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
