<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(3) The agency has established and implemented guidelines for each member of the decision-making body to avoid conflicts
of interest in making decisions; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The agency's dues are paid separately from any dues paid to any related, associated, or affiliated trade association
or membership organization; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The agency's budget is developed and determined by the agency without review by or consultation with any other
entity or organization. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The Secretary considers that any joint use of personnel, services, equipment, or facilities by an accrediting
agency and a related, associated, or affiliated trade association or membership organization does not violate the
provisions of paragraph (c) of this section if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The agency pays the fair market value for its proportionate share of the joint use; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The joint use does not compromise the independence and confidentiality of the accreditation process. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e)(1) Upon request of an accrediting agency described in paragraph (b)(4) of this section, the Secretary waives
the ``separate and independent'' requirements of this section if the agency demonstrates that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The agency has been listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized agency on or before October 1, 1991; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The existing relationship between the agency and the related, associated, or affiliated trade association
or membership organization does not compromise the independence of the accreditation process. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) To demonstrate that the existing relationship between the agency and the related, associated, or affiliated
trade association or membership organization does not compromise the independence of the accreditation process,
the agency must show that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The related, associated, or affiliated trade association or membership organization plays no role in making
or ratifying the accreditation decisions of the agency; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The agency has sufficient budget and administrative autonomy to carry out its accrediting functions; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The agency provides to the related, associated, or affiliated trade association or membership organization
only information it makes available to the public. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.4
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Submission of information to the Secretary by recognized accrediting agencies. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Each accrediting agency recognized by the Secretary shall submit to the Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Reports of final accrediting actions taken by the agency with respect to the institutions and programs it accredits;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) A copy of any annual report prepared by the agency; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) A copy, updated annually, of the agency's directory of accredited institutions and programs; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00064 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(d) A summary of the agency's major accrediting activities during the previous year (an annual data summary), if so
requested by the Secretary to carry out the Secretary's responsibilities related to this part; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) Upon request, information to assist the Secretary in resolving problems with any institution or program accredited
by the agency, provided that the request does not conflict with the agency's policies on confidentiality with respect
to its records on those institutions or programs; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) Any proposed change that might alter the agency's_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Scope of recognition; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Compliance with the requirements of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart B_Recognition and Termination Procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.10
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Application for recognition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) An accrediting agency seeking initial or renewed recognition by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting
agency submits a written application to the Secretary. The application for recognition consists of_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A statement of the agency's requested scope of recognition; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) An analysis of the agency's compliance with the criteria for recognition set forth in this part; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Supporting documentation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(1) An accrediting agency's application for recognition constitutes a grant of authority to the Secretary to
conduct site visits and to gain access to agency records, personnel, and facilities on an announced or unannounced
basis. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary conducts an unannounced site visit only, where necessary in the judgment of the Secretary, to obtain
information to verify that the agency is in compliance with the requirements of this part and the information cannot
be obtained or substantiated in an announced site visit. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Secretary does not make available to the public any confidential agency materials examined by Department
personnel or the Secretary as part of the evaluation of an accrediting agency's application for recognition.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.11
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Preliminary review by the Secretary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Upon receipt of an accrediting agency's application for recognition, the Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Establishes a schedule for the review of the agency by the designated Department official, the National Advisory
Committee on Institutional Quality and Integrity, and the Secretary; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Publishes a notice of the agency's application in the 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Federal Register
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 inviting public comment on the agency's compliance with the requirements for recognition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(1) The designated Department official analyzes the accrediting agency's application to determine whether
the agency satisfies the requirements of this part, taking into account all available relevant information concerning
the compliance of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
agency with the requirements for recognition. The analysis 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
includes_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Site visits, on an announced or unannounced basis, to the agency and, at the Secretary's discretion, representative
institutions or programs it accredits; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Review of public comment and other third-party information solicited by the Secretary, as well as any other information
provided to the Secretary, concerning the performance of the agency in relation to the requirements of this part;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Review of complaints or legal actions involving the agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The designated Department official's evaluation may also include a review of information directly related to
institutions or programs accredited or preaccredited by the agency, relative to their compliance with the accrediting
agency's standards, the effectiveness of the agency's standards, or the agency's application of those standards.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The designated Department official_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Prepares a written analysis of the accrediting agency; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Sends the analysis and all supporting documentation, including all third-party comments received by the Secretary,
to the agency in advance of the Advisory Committee meeting; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Specifies a time period before the Advisory Committee meeting during which the agency may provide the designated
Department official with any written comments on the analysis. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The accrediting agency provides any written comments it chooses to make to the designated Department official
before the expiration of the time period specified in paragraph (c)(3) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The designated Department official provides the Advisory Committee with the accrediting agency's application
and supporting documentation, the designated Department official's analysis of the application, all information
relied upon in developing the analysis, any response by the agency to the analysis, any Department rebuttal to the
agency's response, and any third-party information the Secretary receives regarding the agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f) The designated Department official provides the agency with a copy of any Department rebuttal provided to the
Advisory Committee under paragraph (e) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.12
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Review by the National Advisory Committee on Institutional Quality and Integrity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) The Advisory Committee considers an accrediting agency's application at a public meeting and invites the
designated Department official, the agency, and other interested parties to make oral presentations at the meeting.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The designated Department official arranges for a transcript to be made of the Advisory Committee meeting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) At the conclusion of the meeting, the Advisory Committee recommends that the Secretary approve or deny recognition
of the accrediting agency or defer a decision on the agency's application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00065 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c)(1) If the Advisory Committee recommends recognition, the Advisory Committee also recommends the scope of recognition
for the agency and a recognition period. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the Advisory Committee recommends recognition despite finding that the agency failed to comply with each of
the requirements of this part, the Advisory Committee provides the Secretary with a detailed explanation as to why
it believes the agency's failure to comply with the particular requirement(s) does not require denial or deferral.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If the Advisory Committee recommends denial of recognition, the Advisory Committee specifies the reasons for
the recommendation and the requirements of this part that the agency failed to meet. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) If the Advisory Committee recommends deferral of a decision on the agency's application, the Advisory Committee
specifies the reasons for the recommendation, the requirements of this part that it believes the agency has not met,
and a recommended deferral period. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) After the meeting, the Advisory Committee forwards its written recommendations concerning recognition to the
Secretary. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b, 1145) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.13 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Review and decision by the Secretary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Secretary determines whether to grant national recognition to an applicant accrediting agency based on the
Advisory Committee's recommendation and the full record of the agency's application, including all oral and written
presentations to the Advisory Committee by the agency, the designated Department official, and interested third
parties. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(1) Before making a final decision, the Secretary affords both the designated Department official and the accrediting
agency an opportunity to contest, in writing, the Advisory Committee's recommendation. If either the agency or the
designated Department official wishes to contest the recommendation, that party shall notify the Secretary and
the other party no later than 10 days after the Advisory Committee meeting. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the party contesting the Advisory Committee's recommendation wishes to make a written submission to the Secretary,
the Secretary must receive that submission no later than 30 days after the Advisory Committee meeting. However, the
contesting party may not submit any evidence to the Secretary that it did not submit to the Advisory Committee. The
contesting party shall simultaneously provide a copy of its submission to the other party. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If the noncontesting party wishes to respond in writing to the Secretary, the Secretary must receive that submission
no later than 30 days after the noncontesting party receives the contesting party's submission. However, the noncontesting
party may not submit any evidence to the Secretary that it did not submit to the Advisory Committee. The noncontesting
party shall simultaneously provide a copy of its response to the contesting party.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) If the Advisory Committee's recommendation is contested, the Secretary renders a final decision after taking
into account the two parties' written submissions, if any. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Secretary approves the accrediting agency for national recognition if the Secretary determines that the
agency satisfies each of the requirements contained in this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The Secretary approves the accrediting agency for national recognition even if the agency does not satisfy each
of the requirements contained in this part if the Secretary determines that the agency's effectiveness is not impaired
by the noncompliance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) If the Secretary approves the accrediting agency for national recognition, the Secretary defines-
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The scope of recognition, which may include the_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Geographic area; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Degrees and certificates awarded; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Types of institutions the agency may accredit; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Types of programs the agency may accredit; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Preaccreditation status(es), if any, that the Secretary approves for recognition; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The recognition period, which does not exceed five years. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f)(1) If the Secretary denies recognition to the accrediting agency or grants recognition for a scope narrower than
that requested by the agency, the Secretary indicates in writing the reasons for that decision. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00066 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) The agency described in paragraph (f)(1) of this section may request that the Secretary reconsider the decision
under the provisions of &sect;602.15. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) If the Secretary defers a decision on the accrediting agency's application, the Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Indicates in writing the reasons for the deferral and the deferral period; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Automatically extends any previously granted recognition period until the Secretary reaches a decision on the
renewal application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) If the Secretary does not reach a final decision on an accrediting agency's application for renewal of recognition
before the expiration of the agency's recognition period, the Secretary automatically extends the previously granted
recognition period until the Secretary reaches a decision on the renewal application. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.14 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Limitation, suspension, or termination of recognition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) The Secretary may limit, suspend, or terminate the recognition of an accrediting agency before completion
of its previously granted recognition period if the Secretary determines, after notice and opportunity for a hearing,
that the agency fails or has failed to satisfy any of the requirements of this part. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the agency requests a hearing_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) The hearing is conducted by the Advisory Committee or by a subcommittee of three members of the Advisory Committee,
appointed by the Secretary, if the Secretary determines that a more timely hearing is necessary than can be accommodated
by the schedule of the full Advisory Committee; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The designated Department official arranges for a transcript to be made of the hearing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The designated Department official begins a limitation, suspension, or termination proceeding against an accrediting
agency by sending the agency a notice that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Informs the agency of the Secretary's intent to limit, suspend, or terminate its recognition; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Identifies the alleged violations of the governing regulations that constitute the basis for the action; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Describes the limits to be imposed if the Secretary seeks to limit the accrediting agency; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Specifies the effective date of the limitation, suspension, or termination; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Informs the agency that it may_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Submit to the designated Department official a written response to the notice no later than 30 days after it receives
the notice; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Request a hearing, which shall take place in Washington, DC, before the Advisory Committee or subcommittee if
the agency submits a hearing request to the designated Department official no later than 30 days after it receives
the notice. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c)(1) As part of its response to the limitation, suspension, or termination notice or its hearing request, if any,
the accrediting agency shall identify the issues and facts in dispute and its position with regard to those issues
and facts. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) After receipt of the agency's response and hearing request, if any, the designated Department official_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Transmits the limitation, suspension, or termination notice and the agency's response, if any, to that notice
to the Advisory Committee or subcommittee; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Establishes the date and time of any hearing before the Advisory Committee or subcommittee. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d)(1) Except as provided in paragraph (d)(2) of this section, if a hearing is held, the Advisory Committee or subcommittee
shall allow the designated Department official, the accrediting agency, and any interested party to make an oral
or written presentation. That presentation may include the introduction of written and oral evidence. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) If the designated Department official and the accrediting agency each agree, the Advisory Committee or subcommittee
review shall be based solely on the written materials submitted to it under paragraph (c)(2)(i) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e)(1) After the Advisory Committee or subcommittee reviews the presentations, it shall issue an opinion in which
it_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Makes findings of fact based upon the evidence presented; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Recommends whether a limitation, suspension, or termination of the agency's recognition is warranted; and

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Provides the reasons for that recommendation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00067 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(2) The Advisory Committee or subcommittee shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Transmit its written opinion to the Secretary; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Provide a copy of its opinion to the designated Department official and the accrediting agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(f)(1) After receiving the Advisory Committee's recommendation, the Secretary issues a decision on whether to limit,
suspend, or terminate the agency's recognition, based upon the recommendation of the Advisory Committee and the
full record before the Advisory Committee. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Either the accrediting agency or the designated Department official may appeal the Advisory Committee's recommendation
by filing a notice of appeal with the Secretary within 10 days of receipt of the Advisory Committee's or subcommittee's
recommendation. If either party files an appeal with the Secretary, that party shall simultaneously provide a copy
of the notice of appeal to the other party. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The party appealing the Advisory Committee's or subcommittee's recommendation has 30 days after its receipt
of the recommendation to make a written submission to the Secretary challenging the recommendation. However, the
appealing party may not submit any evidence that was not submitted to the Advisory Committee or subcommittee. The
appealing party shall simultaneously provide a copy of the submission to the other party. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The nonappealing party has 30 days from the date it receives the appealing party's submission to file a written
response to the Secretary regarding the submissions of the appealing party and shall simultaneously provide the
appealing party with a copy of its response. The nonappealing party may not submit any evidence that was not submitted
to the Advisory Committee or subcommittee. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) If the Advisory Committee's or subcommittee's recommendation is appealed, the Secretary renders a final decision
after taking into account that recommendation and the parties' written submissions on appeal. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) If the Secretary limits, suspends, or terminates an accrediting agency's recognition during its recognition
period, the agency may request that the Secretary reconsider this decision under &sect;602.15. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.15 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Requests for reconsideration of the Secretary's decisions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) An accrediting agency may request a reconsideration of a Secretarial decision if the Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Denies its application for recognition; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Does not grant its requested scope of recognition; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Limits, suspends, or terminates the agency's recognition during its recognition period. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The agency may request reconsideration only if the agency demonstrates that_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) It has new information that could not have been presented previously; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The new information is likely to result in reversal of the Secretary's decision. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) To request a reconsideration, the accrediting agency 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Notify the Secretary of its intent no later than 10 days after its receipt of the Secretary's decision; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Submit its written request for reconsideration and the reasons for that request no later than 45 days after receipt
of the Secretary's decision. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c)(1) Within 60 days after receipt of the accrediting agency's written request for reconsideration, the Secretary
renders a final decision based on the information contained in the agency's request and the entire record before both
the Advisory Committee or subcommittee and the Secretary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary may request the opinion of the designated Department official, the Advisory Committee, or the subcommittee
before rendering a final decision. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.16 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Appeals procedures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
An accrediting agency may appeal the Secretary's final decision under this part regarding the agency's recognition
to the Federal courts as a final decision in accordance with applicable Federal law. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

