<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(b) If the Secretary denies recognition to a previously recognized accrediting agency, or limits, suspends, or terminates
its recognition during a previously granted recognition period, the Secretary publishes a notice of that action
in the 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=4 -->
Federal Register 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
and makes available to the public, upon request, the Secretary's determination.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart C_Criteria for Secretarial Recognition 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.20 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Geographic scope of accrediting activities. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that the geographical scope of its accrediting activities covers_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) A State, if the agency is a component of a State government; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) A region of the United States that includes at least three States that are contiguous or in close geographical proximity
to one another; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The United States. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.21 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Administrative and fiscal responsibility. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that it has the administrative and fiscal capability to carry out its accreditation activities in
light of its requested scope of recognition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary considers that an accrediting agency meets the requirements of paragraph (a) of this section if
it has, and will likely continue to have_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Adequate administrative staff to_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Carry out its accrediting responsibilities effectively; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Manage its finances effectively; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Competent and knowledgeable individuals, qualified by experience and training, responsible for on-site evaluation,
policy-making, and decision-making regarding accreditation and preaccreditation status; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Representation on its evaluation, policy, and decision-making bodies of_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) For an institutional accrediting agency, both academic and administrative personnel; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For a programmatic accrediting agency, both educators and practitioners; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Representation of the public on all decision-making bodies; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Clear and effective controls against conflicts of interest or the appearance of conflicts of interest by the agency's
board members, commissioners, evaluation team members, consultants, administrative staff, and other agency representatives;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Adequate financial resources to carry out its accrediting responsibilities, taking into account the funds required
to conduct the range of accrediting activities specified in the requested scope of recognition and the income necessary
to meet the anticipated costs of its activities in the future; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Complete and accurate records of_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Its last two full accreditation or preaccreditation reviews of each institution or program, including self-study
reports, on-site evaluation team reports, institution or program responses to on-site reports, periodic review
reports, and any reports of special review conducted by the agency between regular reviews; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Its decisions with respect to all preaccreditation and accreditation actions, including all adverse actions.

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.22 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Accreditation experience. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that it has adequate experience in accrediting institutions, programs, or both. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary considers that an accrediting agency satisfies the requirements of paragraph (a) of this section
if it has_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Granted accreditation or preaccreditation status to institutions or programs in the geographical area for which
it seeks recognition; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Conducted accreditation activities covering the range of the specific degrees, certificates, and programs
for which it seeks recognition, including_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Granting accreditation or preaccreditation status; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00069 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(ii) Providing technical assistance related to accreditation to institutions, programs, or both; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Policies, evaluative criteria, and procedures, and has made evaluative decisions, that are accepted throughout
the United States by_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Educators and educational institutions; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Licensing bodies, practitioners, and employers in the professional or vocational fields for which the educational
institutions or programs within the agency's jurisdiction prepare their students. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.23 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Application of standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that it consistently applies and enforces written standards that ensure that the education or training
offered by an institution or program is of sufficient quality to achieve, for the duration of any accreditation period
granted by the agency, the stated objective for which it is offered. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Secretary considers that an accrediting agency meets the requirements of paragraph (a) of this section if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The agency's written standards and procedures for accreditation and preaccreditation, if that latter status
is offered, comply with the requirements of this part; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The agency's preaccreditation standards, if offered, are appropriately related to the agency's accreditation
standards, with a limit on preaccreditation status of no more than five years for any institution or program; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The agency's organizations, functions, and procedures include effective controls against the inconsistent
application of its criteria and standards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The agency bases its decisions regarding accreditation or preaccreditation on its published criteria; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) The agency maintains a systematic program of review designed to ensure that its criteria and standards are appropriate
and sufficiently comprehensive to evaluate the quality of the education or training provided by the institutions
or programs it accredits and are relevant to the education or training needs of affected students. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.24 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Accreditation processes.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a)(1) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that it has effective mechanisms for evaluating compliance with its standards and those mechanisms
cover the full range of an institution's or program's offerings, including those offerings conducted at branch campuses
and additional locations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The Secretary considers that an accrediting agency meets the requirements of paragraph (a) of this section if
it meets the requirements contained in paragraphs (b) through (f) of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b)(1) In determining whether to grant initial or renewed accreditation, the accrediting agency evaluates whether
an institution or program_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Maintains clearly specified educational objectives consistent with its mission and appropriate in light of
the degrees or certificates it awards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Is successful in achieving its stated objectives; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Maintains degree and certificate requirements that at least conform to commonly accepted standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Complies with the agency's criteria. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) In reaching its determination to grant initial or renewed accreditation, the accrediting agency_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Requires an in-depth self-study by each institution or program in accordance with guidance provided by the agency,
with particular focus on the assessment of educational quality and the continuing improvement of educational quality;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Conducts at least one on-site review of the institution or program at which the agency obtains sufficient information
to enable it to determine if the institution or program complies with the agency's criteria; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Conducts its own analyses and evaluations of the self-study and supporting documentation furnished by the
institution or program, and any other appropriate information from other sources, to determine whether the institution
or program complies with the agency's standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Provides to the institution or program a detailed written report on its review assessing_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00070 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(A) The institution's or program's compliance with the agency's standards, including areas needing improvement;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The institution's or program's performance with respect to student achievement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) In addition to the on-site visit described in paragraph (b)(2)(ii) of this section, an institutional accrediting
agency whose accreditation enables the institutions it accredits to seek eligibility to participate in Title IV,
HEA programs conducts_during the interval between the agency's award of accreditation or preaccreditation to the
institution or program and the expiration of the accreditation or preaccreditation period_at least one unannounced
on-site review at each institution that provides prebaccalaureate vocational education or training for the purpose
of determining the institution's or program's continued compliance with the agency's standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The accrediting agency_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Monitors institutions or programs throughout the accreditation or preaccreditation period to ensure continuing
compliance with the agency's standards or criteria; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Conducts special evaluations, site visits, or both, as necessary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The accrediting agency regularly reevaluates institutions or programs that have been granted accreditation
or preaccreditation. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=1 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;602.25 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Additions to or substantive changes in educational programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that, except as provided in paragraph (b) of this section, it includes within its previous grant of
accreditation or preaccreditation to an institution an educational program that an institution initially offers,
or substantively changes after that grant of accreditation or preaccreditation, only after_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The institution notifies the accrediting agency of the addition of the new program or the substantive change in
the existing program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The accrediting agency evaluates the new or substantively changed program and determines that it does not adversely
affect the institution's capacity to meet the agency's standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) An accrediting agency may extend accreditation to an educational program that an institution initially offers
or substantively changes after it received the agency's last grant of accreditation or preaccreditation without
specifically evaluating and approving that program if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The institution notifies the agency of that program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The program does not provide prebaccalaureate vocational education. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940124-1-00071 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940124-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(c) For purposes of this section, an accrediting agency defines a substantive change in an educational program, but
the definition must include_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A substantial change in the number of clock or credit hours, the number of weeks, and the content of that program;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) A change in the type of program offered; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) A change in the credential awarded for the successful completion of the program; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) A change from clock hours to credit hours or 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
vice versa.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=20 g=1 f=3 -->
(Authority: 20 U.S.C. 1099b) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=3 -->
&sect;602.26
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=3 -->
Required accreditation standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
(a)(1) To be listed by the Secretary as a nationally recognized accrediting agency, an accrediting agency must demonstrate
to the Secretary that its accreditation or preaccreditation standards, or both, are sufficiently rigorous to ensure
that the agency is a reliable authority as to the quality of the education or training provided by the institutions
or programs it accredits. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) For a programmatic accrediting agency that does not serve as an institutional accrediting agency for any of the
programs it accredits, the standards must address the areas contained in paragraph (b) of this section in terms of
the type and level of the program rather than in terms of the institution. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If none of the institutions an agency accredits participates in any Title IV, HEA program, or if the agency only
accredits programs within institutions accredited by an accrediting agency recognized by the Secretary, the accrediting
agency is not required to have the standards described in paragraphs (b)(7), (b)(8), (b)(10), (b)(12), and (b)(13)
of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) In order to assure that an accrediting agency is a reliable authority as to the quality of the education or training
provided by an institution or program it accredits, the agency must have standards that effectively address the quality
of an institution or program in the following areas: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Curricula. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Faculty. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Facilities, equipment, and supplies. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Fiscal and administrative capacity as appropriate to the specified scale of operations. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The agency shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Have standards addressing the institution's or program's finances and management that enable it to assess an
institution's or program's fiscal and administrative capacity, as appropriate to its scale of operations, for the
purpose of determining whether_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) The institution or program appears able to continue to be an ongoing, economically viable entity; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) The finances of the institution or program appear to be sufficient for it to continue to meet the agency's standards;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Make a determination under this standard_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) When it initially evaluates an institution or program for accreditation or preaccreditation; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) When it periodically reevaluates the institution or program for accreditation or preaccreditation; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Require an institution or program to submit on an annual basis sufficient financial information, which may
include the annual audited financial statement the institution or program submits to the Secretary under the Title
IV, HEA programs, to enable the agency to determine if the financial capacity of the institution threatens the ability
of the institution or program to continue to meet the agency's standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Review, as appropriate on an annual basis, the information obtained under paragraph (b)(4)(iii) of this section
to determine if there is reason to take any follow-up action based on a reduced financial capacity. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Student support services. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Recruiting and admissions practices, academic calendars, catalogs, publications, grading, and advertising.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's recruiting and admissions
practices, academic calendars, catalogs, publications, grading, and advertising in terms of_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Whether the institution's or program's academic calendar, catalogs, publications, and advertising are accurate,
complete, and consistent with actual practice and agency standards, particularly with respect to costs, financial
obligations, refunds, graduation rates, employment prospects, and other statements regarding educational effectiveness;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
