<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Measures of program length in clock hours or credit hours.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's measurement of program length.
In developing these standards, the agency shall take into account such factors as_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Program goals, objectives, and content; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) The types and combinations of instructional methodologies and delivery systems, including outside preparation
as appropriate; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) The knowledge and skills necessary for students to reach competence in the field being taught; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Generally accepted practices in higher education; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v) Any applicable Federal statutes or regulations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Success with respect to student achievement in relation to mission.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's success with respect 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to student achievement. Under these standards, the agency 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Require the institution or program to document and assess the educational achievement of students in verifiable
and consistent ways, such as_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Student grades, grade point averages, theses, or portfolios; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Results of admissions tests for graduate or professional school or other standardized tests; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Transfer rates to institutions offering higher level programs; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D) Job placement rates, completion rates, results of licensing examinations, evaluations by employers, follow-up
studies of alumni, and other recognized measures of educational outcomes; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Require the institution or program to use effectively the information obtained under paragraph (b)(9)(i) of
this section to improve student achievement with respect to the degrees or certificates offered; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Systematically monitor institutional or program performance with respect to student achievement to determine
if performance is consistent with both the institution's or program's mission and objectives and the agency's objective
measures of performance of student achievement; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) For any prebaccalaureate vocational education program accredited by the agency or provided by an institution
the agency accredits, establish minimum quantitative standards for_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(A) Completion rates; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Job placement rates; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Pass rates on State licensing examinations or other appropriate measures of occupational competency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Default rates in the student loan programs established under Title IV of the Act, based on the most recent data provided
by the Secretary.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that require it to evaluate an institution to determine whether the institution is
out of compliance with its accrediting standards if the institution's latest cohort default rate under the Federal
Stafford Loan or Federal Supplemental Loans for Students program_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Equals or exceeds 25 percent; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Has increased significantly in relation to its rate in the previous year. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Record of student complaints received by, or available to, the agency.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that enable it to assess an institution's or program's record of student complaints
received by or made available to the agency. Under these standards, the agency shall_ 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Review student complaints that relate to the agency's standards; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Take appropriate follow-up action with regard to those complaints; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) If considered necessary by the agency, refer complainants to appropriate Federal, State, and other agencies
if the complaints do not relate to the agency's standards; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Require institutions or programs to make available to students the agency's mailing address or telephone number
for complaints. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Compliance with the institution's program responsibilities under Title IV of the Act.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have standards that require institutions to be in compliance with their responsibilities under
the Title IV, HEA programs. The agency's assessment under these standards shall be based on program reviews, financial
and compliance audits, audited financial statements, and any other information that the Secretary provides. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(13) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The institution's practice of making refunds to students.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The agency shall have_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) A refund policy, that must be approved by the Secretary, that provides for a fair and equitable refund to a student
of tuition, fees, and other institutional charges; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Standards that enable it to assess whether an institution complies with its refund policy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

