<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 667.22&blank;Disapproval of State Review Standards
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Under section 494C(d) of the HEA, State-developed standards are ``subject to disapproval by the Secretary.'' In
accordance with that section of the HEA, in &sect;667.22, the Secretary proposes procedures under which the Secretary
evaluates a State's review standards to determine whether to disapprove those standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Specifically, in &sect;667.22(a), a State must submit to the Secretary its review standards along with an explanation
of how each standard was established, including_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) A description of the manner in which institutions in the State were consulted in the development of the standards;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) An explanation of the relationship between each of the State's review standards and the related or comparable

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Title IV, HEA program standards or requirements; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) If applicable, an explanation of the reasons for establishing different review standards for different types
of institutions or educational programs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
In &sect;667.22(b), the Secretary proposes criteria to determine whether to disapprove a State's review standards.
Specifically, the Secretary proposes to disapprove a State's review standards if_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The State does not assure the Secretary that the State's review standards are consistent with the laws and constitution
of that State, as required by section 494C(d) of the HEA; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The State does not submit evidence that the State's review standards were developed in consultation with institutions
in that State, as required in section 494C(d) of the HEA; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The State's review standards do not meet or exceed all of the requirements and cover all the areas described in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section 494C(d) of the HEA and &sect;667.21; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The standards the State quantified under &sect;667.21(b)(4) do not meet certain procedural and statistical
requirements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Finally, in &sect;667.22(c), if the Secretary disapproves a State's review standards, the Secretary proposes to
give the State the reasons for that disapproval and proposes to provide the State an opportunity to either demonstrate
why the Secretary's disapproval was incorrect or submit revised standards that address the reasons for the Secretary's
disapproval. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Secretary invites public comment regarding the proposed evaluation criteria and on additional criteria the
Secretary should use to evaluate a State's review standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
