<!-- PJG ITAG l=52 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart B_Allotment Formula and Funding Procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;667.11 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Allotment formula. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) For each fiscal year for which funds are appropriated to carry out this part: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The Secretary_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Allots $20,000 to Guam, $20,000 to American Samoa, $20,000 to the Northern Mariana Islands, $20,000 to the Virgin
Islands, and $20,000 to the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) Calculates each remaining State's allotment of the remaining funds under paragraph (a)(2) of this section;
and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Notifies each State of its allotment. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Except for Guam, American Samoa, the Northern Mariana Islands, the Virgin Islands, and the Trust Territory of
the Pacific Islands, the Secretary allots those funds to a State by_
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Determining the percentage of institutions participating in a Title IV, HEA program in the State by dividing the
number of institutions located in that State that are certified to participate in a Title IV, HEA program by the total
number of institutions that are certified to participate in all States; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For the latest award year for which information is available, determining the percentage of Title IV, HEA program
funds by dividing the total amount of Title IV, HEA program funds that were made available to students who enrolled
in the institutions in that State that participate in a Title IV, HEA program, or to those students' parents, by the
total amount of Title IV, HEA program funds that were made available to students, or to those student's parents, who
enrolled in institutions that participate in a Title IV, HEA program in all States; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) Averaging the two percentages determined in paragraph (a)(2)(i) and (ii) of this section; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iv) Calculating an ``initial distribution'' by multiplying the average percentage determined in paragraph (a)(2)(iii)
of this section by the amount appropriated to carry out this part less the total amount allotted to Guam, American Samoa,
the Northern Mariana Islands, the Virgin Islands, and the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(v)(A) Determining which States receive less than $50,000 under the initial distribution; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(B) Providing each of those States with $50,000; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(C) Calculating the difference between the $50,000 provided to each of those States and those States' initial distribution;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(vi)(A) Determining which States receive more than $50,000 under the initial distribution; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



